The Administrative Office of the Courts shall provide to the Capital Projects and Bond Oversight Committee, at the committee's January, April, July, and October regular meetings, a status report of all incomplete court facilities projects. The Capital Projects and Bond Oversight Committee shall prescribe data elements for the quarterly status reports. For each project, the status report shall include:
The project title;
The county in which the project is located;
The scope and use allowance authorized for the project in the judicial branch budget, and any increases to the scope or use allowance under KRS 26A.164;
The current status of the project;
Estimated completion date of the project;
An explanation of any delay or major change in the project, including deletion or modification of project components; and
Any other information that the committee requests.
